&quot;Tuscon, I&#39;m reading your location, please let us know if you need
asistance,&quot; Perseus replied.  &quot;Lord Elder, do you read?&quot;

On Fri, Apr 30, 2010 at 9:54 PM, Sandy &lt;magicquartz@...&gt; wrote:

&gt; At the fortress, Tucson Prime gets Lord Perseus&#39;s message and responds.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;This is Tucson Prime, I&#39;m here with Night Shift, Rodimus, Dark Hawk, and
&gt; Perceptor.  We&#39;re in a bit of a bind, I&#39;ve lost my visual capability and I&#39;m
&gt; without my sonar equipment.  But I&#39;m not completely helpless.  We need an
&gt; escape route but I can feel a down draft of air coming inside here..  Not
&gt; sure where it&#39;s from, I&#39;m trying to determine that right now.  Will update
&gt; you soon, Tucson Prime Signing off.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Back at the Ark, on a stasis berth, a tiny Autobot Femme begins to stirr
&gt; from what appears to be quite a long nap.  She takes a deep breath in, and
&gt; slowly opens her big blue optics.  She too, can hear Lord Perseus&#39;s voice
&gt; and tries to reply as best she can.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Lord Perseus....  Huh?  Wha?  I&#39;m - in the Ark...  How&#39;d - I get here?
&gt;  Last thing - I remember ... Tucson..  Ohh no, Tucson!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; She tries to get to her feet, and stumbles onto the floor on her knees.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Gotta - find Tucson!  He - needs me.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; She wanders out of the stasis quarters, and slowly makes her way into the
&gt; main lobby of the Ark, where she finds Lord Elder, and Elita.  She can
&gt; barely keep on her feet, and uses a door way to keep herself upright.  She
&gt; quickly recognizes both Lord Elder and Elita and slowly shuffles over to
&gt; them, but realizes she is still in much need of recovery and Energon.  Her
&gt; nap was long, and her legs had forgotten how to carry her.  She gets to Lord
&gt; Elder, and collapses to her knees once again.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;S&#39;cuse me.  I&#39;m sorry, I - was trying to - see if Tucson was here.  Last -
&gt; thing I remember.. A - blast from behind, and then, nothing. I - heard a
&gt; voice from Lord Perseus..  That&#39;s - what got me out of stasis. &quot;
&gt;
&gt; Slowly she remembers what her legs are for and stands up on them.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Lord Elder, maybe you - know where Tucson is.  I - gotta find him, make
&gt; sure he&#39;s - in one piece, ya know?  After all, he&#39;s kinda, sorta my big
&gt; brother, can&#39;t abandon my only family member can I?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Slowly she regains her perky personality.  She checks over her arrows and
&gt; forearm darts.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;And if I ever set eyes on any of those Decepticreeps, I&#39;m gonna do more
&gt; than just shove a few arrows up their afts, I&#39;ll stick a few up their
&gt; afterburners too for good measure!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Her eyes glow bright blue with recovered resentfulness toward the enemy.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Hmph, especially Scorponok, he deserves it the most. Oooh I hate that
&gt; overgrown arachnid!&quot;
&gt;
